Source: Nelson Examiner and New Zealand Chronicle
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: On Tuesday morning early we started, crossing the Aorere river at the Maori garden, mid-thigh deep, and took the new road leading to the Quartz ranges, as far as section peg 28, thence struck off to section peg 88, and thence took a west-south-west course to the river, which is a broad stream, beautifully edged with fine timber.
